loped nations. Madland's practical advice in Re-Union extends to a proposal for how to implement the changes necessary to shift the current paradigm. This powerful call to action speaks directly to the workers affected by these policies—the very people seeking to have their voices recognized in a system that attempts to silence them.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aIndustrial relationszUnited States. 0aLabor policyzUnited States. 0aLabor unionszUnited Statesy21st century. 4aGeneral Economics. 4aPolitical Science & Political History. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / Labor & Industrial Relations.2bisacsh  aSectoral bargaining, Ghent system, union modernization, union revival, new labor system.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertCornell University Press Complete eBook-Package 2021z978311073908408iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2021 Englishz978311075400108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2021z9783110753776oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Political Science 2021 Englishz978311075417908iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Political Science 2021z9783110753943oZDB-23-PLW40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9781501755392?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781501755392423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781501755392/original  a978-3-11-073908-4  Cornell University Press Complete eBook-Package 2021b2021  a978-3-11-075400-1  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2021 Englishb2021  a978-3-11-075417-9  EBOOK PACKAGE Political Science 2021 Englishb2021  aEBA_EMB  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-DGGb2021  aZDB-23-PLWb2021